definitions.definition: A survey of people , usually statistically analyzed to gauge wider public opinion .
A formal vote held in order to ascertain the most popular choice .
examples: The student council had a poll to see what people want served in the cafeteria.

definitions.definition: A polling place ( usually as plural , polling places )
The result of the voting, the total number of votes recorded.
( now rare outside veterinary contexts ) The head , particularly the scalp or pate upon which hair ( normally ) grows .
( in extended senses of the above ) A mass of people , a mob or muster , considered as a head count .
The broad or butt end of an axe or a hammer .
The pollard or European chub , a kind of fish .

definitions.definition: One who does not try for honors at university, but is content to take a degree merely; a passman .

main_definition: ( UK , dated , Cambridge University ) One who does not try for honors at university, but is content to take a degree merely; a passman .
